    <!-- Pro Tip callout -->
    <div class="border-l-4 border-brand bg-white rounded-r-xl pl-5 pr-4 py-4 my-6 shadow-card">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-1">Pro tip</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#475569] leading-relaxed">When auditing your backlink profile, check which linking domains are still indexed by Google. Any that aren't: remove their value from your attribution. A link on a deindexed site contributes nothing to the citation pattern AI systems read.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- PROSE BLOCK 4: Evidence -->
    <div class="prose prose-lg text-body max-w-none space-y-6 leading-relaxed">

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mt-10 mb-4">The Evidence</h2>
      <p>
        Google's March 2024 core update and every Helpful Content Update since have pushed harder on source authority and editorial quality. Marketplace domains have been purged in waves.
      </p>
      <p>
        Retrieval-augmented generation is the architecture behind every major AI answer engine. Retrieval systems are tuned to weight sources by the authority signals of their domains. Sources that appear across multiple well-established publications get weighted more heavily than sources that appear once across many low-authority sites.
      </p>
      <p>
        On the pricing side, <a href="/resources/the-cost-of-authority" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">our longitudinal analysis</a> of agency-managed link prices 2020–2026 shows the agency tier barely keeping pace with inflation while publisher-direct prices have tripled. The market is pricing in what indexation enforcement is doing to marketplace link value. Manufactured authority is getting cheaper because its shelf life is collapsing. Earned authority is getting more expensive because the durable supply is capped.
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- Further Reading callout -->
    <div class="border-l-4 border-brand bg-white rounded-r-xl pl-5 pr-4 py-4 my-6 shadow-card">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-1">Further reading</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#475569] leading-relaxed"><a href="/resources/the-cost-of-authority" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">The Cost of Authority</a>: our pricing analysis of 140,000+ publisher listings across six years, showing exactly how agency-managed and publisher-direct link prices have moved 2020–2026.</p>
    </div>

